ğŸ¨ How to Copy Files Properly
Method 1: Using Text Editor (Recommended)

    Open VS Code / Notepad++ / Sublime Text
    Create new file (Ctrl+N)
    Scroll to the artifact in our conversation
    Click on the artifact to expand it
    Copy all the code (Ctrl+A, then Ctrl+C)
    Paste into your editor (Ctrl+V)
    Save with correct filename (e.g., server.js)
    Repeat for all files

Method 2: Using Command Line

Windows (PowerShell):
powershell

# Navigate to project folder
cd C:\Projects\justice-client-portal

# Create files
New-Item -Path "server.js" -ItemType File
New-Item -Path "package.json" -ItemType File
New-Item -Path "public\front.html" -ItemType File
# ... etc

# Then open each file and paste the content
notepad server.js

Mac/Linux:
bash

# Navigate to project folder
cd ~/Projects/justice-client-portal

# Create files
touch server.js package.json Dockerfile docker-compose.yml
touch public/front.html public/new.html public/update.html public/find.html

# Then open and paste content
nano server.js  # or use vim, code, etc.

