ğŸš€ Choose Your Setup Method
Option A: Docker Setup (Easiest - Recommended)

Requirements:

    Docker Desktop installed

Steps:
bash

cd justice-client-portal

# Start everything
docker-compose up -d

# Wait 30 seconds, then open browser
# http://localhost:3000

That's it! âœ… No MySQL installation needed!
Option B: Traditional Setup

Requirements:

    Node.js installed
    MySQL installed

Steps:
bash

cd justice-client-portal

# 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Create database
mysql -u root -p
CREATE DATABASE law_department;
exit;

# 3. Edit server.js line 17 (set MySQL password)
# password: 'your_mysql_password_here'

# 4. Start server
npm start

# 5. Open browser
# http://localhost:3000

